TY  - JOUR
AU  - Ridder, Geert
T1  - The Non-Parametric Identification of Generalized Accelerated Failure-Time Models
PY  - 1990
Y1  - 1990/04/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297376
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 57
IS  - 2
SP  - 167
EP  - 181
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - We consider a class of models that generalizes the popular Mixed Proportional Hazard (MPH) model for duration data: the Generalized Accelerated Failure-Time (GAFT) model. We show that the GAFT model is non-parametrically identified (up to a normalization). We then reconsider the non-parametric identification of the MPH model. We show that the class of MPH models is not closed under normalization. This implies that a finite mean of the mixing distribution is a necessary condition for (non-parametric) identification of the MPH model. It is impossible to test this hypothesis without imposing arbitrary restrictions on the base-line hazard and/or the regression function.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297376
ER  - 



